(227, 1, '2016-08-01 16:26:54', '2016-08-01 15:26:54', 'Creating a members only e-commerce website with pre-set users and having controll over the new users approval? Using WooCommerce with its registration form with a few added fields does the job perfectly. The only issue is that when a user completes the form, WooCommerce checks for empty fields and logs the user in straight away, skipping the administration approval. Why dont we add \'<a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-approve-user/">New User Approve</a>\'?\r\n\r\nThe code below doesn\'t need changing, you need to have <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-approve-user/">WP Approve User</a> installed and active, the rest can be "copy - paste" in your functions.php. Please, read the code and follow my explanation below:\r\n<pre class="lang:php decode:true  ">function user_autologout(){\r\n if ( is_user_logged_in() ) {\r\n  $current_user = wp_get_current_user();\r\n  $user_id = $current_user-&gt;ID;\r\n\r\n  $approved_status = get_user_meta($user_id, \'wp-approve-user\', true);\r\n\r\n  //if the user hasn\'t been approved yet by WP Approve User plugin, log them out\r\n  if ( $approved_status == 1 ){\r\n   return $redirect_url;\r\n  }\r\n  else {\r\n   wp_logout();\r\n   return get_permalink(woocommerce_get_page_id(\'myaccount\')) . "?approved=false";\r\n  }\r\n }\r\n}\r\nadd_action(\'woocommerce_registration_redirect\', \' user_autologout\', 2);\r\n\r\nfunction registration_message(){\r\n $not_approved_message = \'\r\n   Send in your registration application today!\r\n   NOTE: Your account will be held for moderation and you will be unable to login until it is approved.\r\n \';\r\n\r\n if( isset($_REQUEST[\'approved\']) ){\r\n  $approved = $_REQUEST[\'approved\'];\r\n  if ($approved == \'false\') echo \'\r\n    Registration successful! You will be notified upon approval of your account.\r\n  \';\r\n  else echo $not_approved_message;\r\n  }\r\n else echo $not_approved_message;\r\n}\r\nadd_action(\' woocommerce_before_customer_login_form\', \' registration_message\', 2);</pre>\r\nThe actions gets called once the woocommerce form is submited and checked. The user data is stored in the database which is followed by the function that checks if the user has been approved by the admin ( This is why we usedÂ <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-approve-user/">WP Approve User</a>). If its not, it signs the user out it and notifies by echoing a message on the page, showing that the user registration status is on \'pending\' and it needs to be approved before being able to log in.\r\n<h3>Removing auto generated password by New User Approve</h3>\r\nTo prevent some future confusion with the automatically generated password, the plugin provides a solution to disable creating one and leaving that in user\'s hands. It usually triggers itself when the user is activated and it overrides the custom password added by the user in the registration process. You might also need to check the e-mail templates and remove/retouch that message there as well. For more help, don\'t hesitate to contact me!\r\n<div class="code">\r\n<pre class="lang:php decode:true ">function ignore_new_user_autopass() {\r\n return true;\r\n}\r\nadd_filter( \'new_user_approve_bypass_password_reset\', \'ignore_new_user_autopass\' );</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Remove WooCommerce auto-login while using New User Approve', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'remove-woocommerce-auto-login-while-using-new-user-approve', '', '', '2017-07-16 18:26:16', '2017-07-16 17:26:16', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/ivelin.me//?p=227', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(228, 1, '2017-07-16 11:26:54', '2017-07-16 10:26:54', 'The client\'s requirement was to have a woocommerce website only for members which will be approved by the admin (website owner). Using the default woocommerce registration form with a few added fields does the job perfectly. The only issue is that after the user enters the details and submits the form, woocommerce only checks for empty fields and logs the user in straight away, skipping the admin approval. The code below doesn\'t need changing, you need to have WP Approve User installed and active, the rest can be "copy - paste" in your functions.php and I will explain it in more details below:\r\n<div class="code">\r\n\r\nfunction user_autologout(){\r\nif ( is_user_logged_in() ) {\r\n$current_user = wp_get_current_user();\r\n$user_id = $current_user-&gt;ID;\r\n\r\n$approved_status = get_user_meta($user_id, \'wp-approve-user\', true);\r\n\r\n//if the user hasn\'t been approved yet by WP Approve User plugin, log them out\r\nif ( $approved_status == 1 ){\r\nreturn $redirect_url;\r\n}\r\nelse{\r\nwp_logout();\r\nreturn get_permalink(woocommerce_get_page_id(\'myaccount\')) . "?approved=false";\r\n}\r\n}\r\n}\r\n\r\nadd_action(\'woocommerce_registration_redirect\', \' user_autologout\', 2);\r\n\r\nfunction registration_message(){\r\n$not_approved_message = \'\r\n<p class="registration">Send in your registration application today!\r\nNOTE: Your account will be held for moderation and you will be unable to login until it is approved.</p>\r\n\';\r\n\r\nif( isset($_REQUEST[\'approved\']) ){\r\n$approved = $_REQUEST[\'approved\'];\r\nif ($approved == \'false\') echo \'\r\n<p class="registration successful">Registration successful! You will be notified upon approval of your account.</p>\r\n\';\r\nelse echo $not_approved_message;\r\n}\r\nelse echo $not_approved_message;\r\n}\r\nadd_action(\' woocommerce_before_customer_login_form\', \' registration_message\', 2);\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nWith a few words, the action gets activated once the form is submited and checked. The user data is stored in the database and the code checks if the user has been approved by the plugin. If its not, it signs the user out it and notifies by printing a message on the page saying that the user registration status is on \'pending\' and it needs to be approved before being able to access their account. Copy the code in your functions.php and give it a play. Before that we are not finished yet, now we have got to do the second part of the job before we consider this as completed..\r\n<h3>Removing auto generated password by New User Approve</h3>\r\nI really don\'t see the point why a user should get a generated password while they can choose their own while filling the registration form. This is a function provided by New User Approve which triggers itself when the user is activated and it overrides the custom password. That might only bring confusion. Anyway, the code below doesn\'t need customisation and disables that auto-generating password which is send to the user. You might also need to check the e-mail templates and remove/retouch that message there as well. For more help, don\'t hesitate to contact me!\r\n<div class="code">\r\n\r\nfunction ignore_new_user_autopass() {\r\nreturn true;\r\n}\r\nadd_filter( \'new_user_approve_bypass_password_reset\', \'ignore_new_user_autopass\' );\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Remove WooCommerce auto-login while using New User Approve', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '227-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-07-16 11:26:54', '2017-07-16 10:26:54', '', 227, 'http://localhost:8888/ivelin.me//227-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
